Reinforcement Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Reinforcement Learning is present in the text as the paper discusses the acquisition of a non-reactive mobot through a learning regime. The agent's behavior is shaped by the consequences of its actions, which is a key characteristic of reinforcement learning. 

Probabilistic Methods are also present in the text as the paper discusses the use of a specific sequence of dynamic states to facilitate the acquisition of the behavior. This involves manipulating the probabilities of the agent encountering certain states in order to guide its learning.
